   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Grokking: Weight Averaging & Distillation Experiment\n",
    "\n",
    "Reproduces the grokking experiment (Power et al., 2022) on modular division (mod 97), then compares:\n",
    "- **Baseline**: single model trained on full data\n",
    "- **4 Specialists**: each trained on 25% of the data\n",
    "- **Weight Averaged**: average specialist weights, fine-tune on full data\n",
    "- **Distilled**: knowledge distillation from specialists into a fresh student\n",
    "\n",
    "All methods use the **same total compute budget** for fair comparison."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Cell 1: Install Dependencies"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "!pip install -q pytorch_lightning mod sympy blobfile"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Cell 2: Clone Repo & Apply Fixes"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os, sys\n",
    "\n",
    "REPO_DIR = '/kaggle/working/grok'\n",
    "if not os.path.exists(REPO_DIR):\n",
    "    !git clone https://github.com/openai/grok {REPO_DIR}\n",
    "\n",
    "sys.path.insert(0, REPO_DIR)\n",
    "os.chdir(REPO_DIR)\n",
    "print(f'Repo at: {REPO_DIR}')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Cell 3: Apply Validation Bug Fix\n",
    "\n",
    "The original code's `on_validation_epoch_end` never fires in Lightning 2.x, so val_loss, val_accuracy, full_train_acc, and paramnorm_* are never logged. This fix ensures validation runs every epoch."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import re\n",
    "\n",
    "TRAINING_FILE = os.path.join(REPO_DIR, 'grok', 'training.py')\n",
    "with open(TRAINING_FILE, 'r') as f:\n",
    "    code = f.read()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Fix 1: validation_step — move next_epoch_to_eval update before skip, append {} on skip\n",
    "old_val_step = '''    def validation_step(self, batch, batch_idx):\n",
    "        \"\"\"\n",
    "        Used by pytorch_lightning\n",
    "        Runs one forward validation pass on one batch\n",
    "\n",
    "        :param batch: The batch of equations to process\n",
    "        :param batch_idx: which batch this is in the epoch.\n",
    "        :returns: a dict with val_loss, val_accuracy, probabilities of solutions,\n",
    "                  attentions, and values\n",
    "        \"\"\"\n",
    "        if self.next_epoch_to_eval < self.current_epoch:\n",
    "            self.next_epoch_to_eval = self.current_epoch\n",
    "        if self.current_epoch != self.next_epoch_to_eval:\n",
    "            return {}\n",
    "        with torch.no_grad():\n",
    "            loss, accuracy, coeff, x_lhs, y_hat_rhs, attentions, values = self._step(\n",
    "                batch=batch, batch_idx=batch_idx, train=False\n",
    "            )\n",
    "        output = {\n",
    "            \"partial_val_loss\": coeff * loss,\n",
    "            \"partial_val_accuracy\": coeff * accuracy,\n",
    "            \"y_hat_rhs\": y_hat_rhs,\n",
    "            \"partial_attentions\": attentions,\n",
    "            \"partial_values\": values,\n",
    "        }\n",
    "        if self.current_epoch == 0:\n",
    "            output[\"x_lhs\"] = x_lhs\n",
    "\n",
    "        self._val_step_outputs.append(output)\n",
    "        return output'''\n",
    "\n",
    "new_val_step = '''    def validation_step(self, batch, batch_idx):\n",
    "        \"\"\"\n",
    "        Used by pytorch_lightning\n",
    "        Runs one forward validation pass on one batch\n",
    "\n",
    "        :param batch: The batch of equations to process\n",
    "        :param batch_idx: which batch this is in the epoch.\n",
    "        :returns: a dict with val_loss, val_accuracy, probabilities of solutions,\n",
    "                  attentions, and values\n",
    "        \"\"\"\n",
    "        # Unconditionally advance next_epoch_to_eval so it never gets stuck\n",
    "        if self.next_epoch_to_eval < self.current_epoch:\n",
    "            self.next_epoch_to_eval = self.current_epoch\n",
    "        if self.current_epoch != self.next_epoch_to_eval:\n",
    "            self._val_step_outputs.append({})\n",
    "            return {}\n",
    "        with torch.no_grad():\n",
    "            loss, accuracy, coeff, x_lhs, y_hat_rhs, attentions, values = self._step(\n",
    "                batch=batch, batch_idx=batch_idx, train=False\n",
    "            )\n",
    "        output = {\n",
    "            \"partial_val_loss\": coeff * loss,\n",
    "            \"partial_val_accuracy\": coeff * accuracy,\n",
    "            \"y_hat_rhs\": y_hat_rhs,\n",
    "            \"partial_attentions\": attentions,\n",
    "            \"partial_values\": values,\n",
    "        }\n",
    "        if self.current_epoch == 0:\n",
    "            output[\"x_lhs\"] = x_lhs\n",
    "\n",
    "        self._val_step_outputs.append(output)\n",
    "        return output'''\n",
    "\n",
    "assert old_val_step in code, 'validation_step pattern not found'\n",
    "code = code.replace(old_val_step, new_val_step)\n",
    "print('Fixed validation_step')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Fix 2: on_validation_epoch_end — remove next_epoch_to_eval update (moved to validation_step), fix checkpoint_path\n",
    "old_val_epoch_end_header = '''        if validation_is_real:\n",
    "            self.next_epoch_to_eval = max(\n",
    "                int(1.02 * self.next_epoch_to_eval), self.next_epoch_to_eval + 1\n",
    "            )'''\n",
    "assert old_val_epoch_end_header in code, 'on_validation_epoch_end header not found'\n",
    "code = code.replace(old_val_epoch_end_header, '        if validation_is_real:')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Fix checkpoint_path fallback\n",
    "old_ckpt = '''            self.trainer.save_checkpoint(\n",
    "                os.path.join(\n",
    "                    self.hparams.checkpoint_path,\n",
    "                    \"epoch_\" + str(self.current_epoch) + \".ckpt\",\n",
    "                )\n",
    "            )'''\n",
    "new_ckpt = '''            ckpt_path = getattr(self.hparams, \"checkpoint_path\", None) or os.path.join(\n",
    "                self.hparams.logdir, \"checkpoints\"\n",
    "            )\n",
    "            os.makedirs(ckpt_path, exist_ok=True)\n",
    "            self.trainer.save_checkpoint(\n",
    "                os.path.join(\n",
    "                    ckpt_path,\n",
    "                    \"epoch_\" + str(self.current_epoch) + \".ckpt\",\n",
    "                )\n",
    "            )'''\n",
    "assert old_ckpt in code, 'checkpoint_path pattern not found'\n",
    "code = code.replace(old_ckpt, new_ckpt)\n",
    "print('Fixed on_validation_epoch_end')\n",
    "\n",
    "with open(TRAINING_FILE, 'w') as f:\n",
    "    f.write(code)\n",
    "\n",
    "print('All fixes applied to grok/training.py')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Add split_n_ways to data.py (not in original OpenAI repo)\n",
    "DATA_FILE = os.path.join(REPO_DIR, 'grok', 'data.py')\n",
    "with open(DATA_FILE, 'r') as f:\n",
    "    data_code = f.read()\n",
    "\n",
    "if 'split_n_ways' not in data_code:\n",
    "    # Find where to insert (after the __len__ method)\n",
    "    insert_marker = '    def __getitem__(self, idx: int) -> Dict[str, torch.Tensor]:'\n",
    "    split_n_ways_code = '''\n",
    "    @classmethod\n",
    "    def split_n_ways(\n",
    "        cls,\n",
    "        dataset: \"ArithmeticDataset\",\n",
    "        n: int,\n",
    "        seed: int = 42,\n",
    "    ) -> List[\"ArithmeticDataset\"]:\n",
    "        \"\"\"Partition an existing dataset into n disjoint shards.\"\"\"\n",
    "        gen = torch.Generator()\n",
    "        gen.manual_seed(seed)\n",
    "        perm = torch.randperm(len(dataset.data), generator=gen)\n",
    "        chunks = torch.chunk(perm, n)\n",
    "        result = []\n",
    "        for chunk in chunks:\n",
    "            shard = cls.__new__(cls)\n",
    "            shard.tokenizer = dataset.tokenizer\n",
    "            shard.name = dataset.name\n",
    "            shard.train = True\n",
    "            shard.data = dataset.data[chunk]\n",
    "            result.append(shard)\n",
    "        return result\n",
    "\n",
    "'''\n",
    "    # Insert after __getitem__ method\n",
    "    idx = data_code.find(insert_marker)\n",
    "    if idx != -1:\n",
    "        # Find the end of this method (next @classmethod or end of class)\n",
    "        rest = data_code[idx + len(insert_marker):]\n",
    "        end_idx = rest.find('    @classmethod')\n",
    "        if end_idx == -1:\n",
    "            end_idx = rest.find('    # @')\n",
    "        if end_idx == -1:\n",
    "            end_idx = 500  # default insert point\n",
    "        insert_pos = idx + len(insert_marker) + end_idx\n",
    "        data_code = data_code[:insert_pos] + split_n_ways_code + data_code[insert_pos:]\n",
    "    with open(DATA_FILE, 'w') as f:\n",
    "        f.write(data_code)\n",
    "    print('Added split_n_ways to data.py')\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print('split_n_ways already in data.py')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Add import for ArithmeticIterator to multi_training.py\n",
    "MULTI_FILE = os.path.join(REPO_DIR, 'grok', 'multi_training.py')\n",
    "with open(MULTI_FILE, 'r') as f:\n",
    "    multi_code = f.read()\n",
    "if 'from grok.data import ArithmeticDataset' in multi_code and 'ArithmeticIterator' not in multi_code:\n",
    "    multi_code = multi_code.replace(\n",
    "        'from grok.data import ArithmeticDataset',\n",
    "        'from grok.data import ArithmeticDataset, ArithmeticIterator'\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    with open(MULTI_FILE, 'w') as f:\n",
    "        f.write(multi_code)\n",
    "    print('Added ArithmeticIterator import to multi_training.py')\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print('multi_training.py imports already correct')
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Cell 4: Imports & Configuration"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import torch\n",
    "import copy\n",
    "import json\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib\n",
    "matplotlib.use('Agg')\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
